---
title: Human-readable post title
category: primary category ID
tags: comma-separated list of tags to index by
date: (optional - if this field doesn't exist, it will be auto-populated by the site the first time its loaded)
body: |
  any indented text that follows will be included in the post body.
  this can wrap over multiple lines.
  <br> tags are inserted in the cached copy where newlines exist in this file
  images can be included inline with one of the following strings:
  img:foo.jpg:wrap
  img:bar.gif:center
  the above two directives will be translated into html to embed respective image names from /static/images/ into the post.
  images tagged with :wrap will be left-aligned and text will wrap around them, while :center will display as a centered block item.
